Targets are defined in BUILD files, relative to the top-level WORKSPACE.
:baz
  The target baz, in the same BUILD file
//foo/bar:baz
  The target baz, defined in foo/bar/BUILD
//foo/bar
  syntactic sugar for //foo/bar:bar
//foo/bar:all
  Every target in foo/bar/BUILD
//foo/bar/...
  Every target in foo/bar/**/BUILD

Alternately:
  “//” means the WORKSPACE directory
  “:” means the BUILD file
